Since the kickoff to this 2023 season, I’ve seen posts on Chief Delphi with teams showing off their robots and protectors on their precious Mk4Is. Today while we were wiring our robot, I thought we should do the same thing, but with a low-profile design that’s able to hold our excess wires and look cool. I hopped onto fusion and a few minutes later had this beauty, it’s able to be cut out of 1/8" lexan and then folded over at the bottom of the triangle. Later we plan on cutting vinyl decals to lay over them, but now it’s back to wiring.

-Griffin

That could be an option for added protection, but I don’t have any experience with honeycomb panels. This plate was really only meant for internal protection and added room for wire mounting on the inside.

In the future, it could be beneficial to remake this but with bends that create a wall on the outward-facing side of the swerve module since I would like to keep this whole design to just a single bolted-on plate for ease of access and to make it on our router.
